hopobject.body: Hold the line, please en.megapharm.al Rubio, who has taken on the largest role in negotiating immigration reform, garners top support from Hispanic voters who say they would vote in a Republican primary. His 29 percent leads Christie at 14 percent, Bush's 13 percent, Ryan's 11 percent and Paul's 9 percent. But many of the Republican candidates are largely unknown by Latino voters, which leaves plenty of room for movement.
